# UJL Clean Code: Naming and Intent

## Goal

Names should explain domain intent, not implementation details.

## Must

- Use names that reflect UJL domain concepts (`module`, `slot`, `field`, `library`, `overlay`, `composer`).
- Prefer explicit verbs for actions (`insertModule`, `updateField`, `toggleFullscreen`) over vague verbs (`handle`, `process`, `do`).
- Avoid ambiguous abbreviations in exported symbols.
- Rename misleading variables when logic evolves.

## Should

- Keep naming consistent across `types`, `core`, `crafter`, and adapters.
- Mirror existing package terminology from README/docs and public APIs.

## Avoid

- `data`, `item`, `value`, `tmp`, `obj` as long-lived identifiers.
- Prefixes that expose implementation noise (`newData2`, `realStore`, `finalResult`).

## Allowed Exceptions

- Short loop/index identifiers in very small local scopes.
- Widely established abbreviations (`id`, `url`, `html`, `ast`).
